We reiterated the recommendations that Management

require the Inventory Committee to (i) conduct a physical count on the property, plant and equipment to determine the existence and condition of the PPEs; (ii) submit the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) duly reconciled with the accounting and property records;

require the Municipal Accountant and the GSO to (i) maintain subsidiary records for PPE items such as PPE ledger cards and property cards, respectively, starting with current year acquisitions until all items are covered; and (ii) reconcile the respective records of the Accounting Office and Property Officer on PPE;

