We recommended that management strengthen its internal controls on compliance with laws, rules and regulations by:

purchasing common use supplies from the DBM-PS to avail of the most advantageous price. If the items to be procured are not available thereat, attach a certification that the items are not available at DBM-PS and a BAC Resolution recommending and justifying to the HOPE the use of alternative mode of procurement and approval by the HOPE of the BAC Resolution recommending award of contract;

adhering to the Revised IRR of RA 9184, particularly, Sections 10 and 48.2 regarding conduct of public bidding on procurement of goods and services exceeding P100,000.00, and Section 54.1 by avoiding splitting to avail of the least possible costs on procured goods and services thus preventing overpricing and sanctions for violation of the procurement law;

strictly complying with the GPPB Resolution No. 16-2016 by posting in the Municipality and PhilGEPS websites the RFQ, PO/WO and Approved Budget for the Contract (ABC) of items to be procured to attract more bidders/suppliers and promote competition in the conduct of alternative modes of procurement.  The awards of contract to winning suppliers should also be posted to provide information on items with the lowest price in the market; and

attaching a printed copy of RFQs/POs/JOs/awards of contract, as posted in the Municipality and PhilGEPS websites, to the Disbursement Vouchers for audit purposes.

We recommended that the Local School Board -

come up with a strategic prioritization plan in the allocation of the SEF to public schools taking into consideration the most important needs of the students and not just for repairs of school facilities for optimum attainment of the intent of the fund in accordance with DepEd-DDBM-DLG JC 2017-001; 

along with the BAC, adhere to the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR particularly, Sections 10 and 48.2 regarding the conduct of public bidding on procurement of goods and services exceeding P100,000.00, and Section 54.1 by avoiding splitting to avail of the least possible costs on procured goods and services, thus preventing overpricing and sanctions for violation of the procurement law and with the GPPB Resolution No. 09-2009 by posting in the Municipality and PhilGEPS websites the RFQ, PO/WO and Approved Budget for the Contract (ABC) of items to be procured to attract more bidders/suppliers and ensure competitiveness in the conduct of alternative modes of procurement.  The awards of contract to winning suppliers should also be posted to provide information on items with the lowest price in the market;

require the Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Accountant to submit to the LSB a certified statement of the actual income and expenditures of the SEF in the preceding fiscal year and the current year on the prescribed period; 

require the Municipal Accountant to (i) ensure that the necessary documents are attached to the disbursement vouchers before payment to suppliers is made; and (ii) submit to the Audit Team the necessary documents on the payment of repairs and maintenance of school buildings for its evaluation.

